steps.instruction:
1. Preheat oven to 350F
2. Place ribs on foil in a single layer
3. Season ribs by rubbing the seasoning into them on both sides
4. Wash your hands
5. Bring up the ends of the foil and double fold ends to seal. Do this to both sides to completely seal
6. Place on baking sheet
7. Bake for 2 hours
8. You can finish them on the grill for best flavor (optional)
9. Combine the sauce and the cider
10. Brush the ribs
11. Cook on the grill (if you'd like) for 3 to 4 minutes
